README for c.vim (Version 2.6) / 07.03.2002

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FILES
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

README                this file

c.vim                 The C/C++ plugin for GVIM. 
                      Copy this file to your local plugin directory: ~/.vim/plugin/c.vim .
                      
costumization.gvimrc  Additional settings I use in .gvimrc: hot keys, font, dictionary, ..
                      The file is commented. Append it to your .gvimrc if you like.

costumization.vimrc   Additional settings I use in .vimrc: incremental search, tabstop,..
                      The file is commented. Append it to your .vimrc if you like.

word.list             A file with words used for automatic word completion. 
                      This file contains:
                      - All C and C++ keywords.
                      - Words from the table of content of K&R. 
                        They appear frequently in comments.
                      - Method names and type names from the Standard Template Library. 
                      Copy this file to the directory  ~/.vim/ if you want to use it.
                      This file is referenced in costumization.gvimrc .
                      >> The word list is an add on; c.vim does not depend on it. <<

